A nine-year-old boy, Sabiu Sani from Babale Fulani in Taura Local Government Area of Jigawa State, is dead. He passed away after drowning in a pond in the outskirt of the settlement. 25-year-old comedian drowns in Cross River during birthday celebration
ASP Lawan Shiisu, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) confirmed the incident in a statement on Wednesday. The spokesman said it occurred on Monday at 10:00 a.m., after the deceased went to swim near the village. Another teenager drowns in Kano pond
The District Head of Taura, Alhaji Nura Usman reported that mishap to the police. A team of policeman headed to the scene and recovered the corpse. Shiisu added that the body has been handed over to the parents for burial.